encyclopedia.netherite.body=Molten Netherite can only be poured into blocks or ingots, for all other parts Diamond must be upgraded in a Smithing Table.%1%1Tool Head%1%1Durability: 1420%1Harvest Tier: Netherite%1Mining Speed: 8%1Attack Damage: 3%1%1Tool Handle/Guard%1%1Durability: 2.5x%1Mining Speed: 1.8x%1Attack Damage: 2x%1Trait: Guarding
encyclopedia.pickaxe.body=The sturdy Pickaxe is your go-to tool for mining valuable ores and tough blocks like stone. %1%1It's not the fanciest tool, but it gets the job done, breaking blocks with ease.%1%1§oRequires the Tinkers' Station to craft.
encyclopedia.pig_iron.body=Tool Head%1%1Durability: 580%1Harvest Tier: Diamond%1Mining Speed: 6%1Attack Damage: 2.5%1%1Tool Handle/Guard%1%1Durability: 1.1x%1Mining Speed: 0.85x%1Attack Damage: 1.1x%1Trait: Tasty
encyclopedia.queens_slime.body=Tool Head%1%1Durability: 1650%1Harvest Tier: Netherite%1Mining Speed: 6%1Attack Damage: 2%1%1Tool Handle/Guard%1%1Durability: 1.35x%1Mining Speed: 0.9x%1Attack Damage: 0.95x%1Trait: Bounce
encyclopedia.rose_gold.body=Tool Head%1%1Durability: 175%1Harvest Tier: Gold%1Mining Speed: 9%1Attack Damage: 1%1%1Tool Handle/Guard%1%1Durability: 0.6x%1Mining Speed: 1.2x%1Attack Damage: 1x%1Trait: Experienced
encyclopedia.shoel.body=This innovative tool combines the functionalities of a Shovel and a Hoe%1%1Not only can you dig Dirt paths with ease, but you can also till the ground for planting by simply sneaking while using it.%1%1§oRequires the Tinkers' Station to craft.
encyclopedia.slimesteel.body=Tool Head%1%1Durability: 1040%1Harvest Tier: Diamond%1Mining Speed: 6%1Attack Damage: 2.5%1%1Tool Handle/Guard%1%1Durability: 1.2x%1Mining Speed 1x%1Attack Damage: 1x%1Trait: Stuck
encyclopedia.stone.body=Tool Head%1%1Durabilty: 130%1Harvest Tier: Stone%1Mining Speed: 4%1Attack Damage: 1%1%1Tool Handle/Guard%1%1Durabilty: 0.9x%1Attack Damage: 1x%1Trait: Summoner
encyclopedia.sword.body=Sure, swords excel at vanquishing foes, but that's not all they can do!%1%1They also act as handy tools for swiftly breaking down things like bamboo and cobwebs, making them a versatile companion on your adventures.%1%1§oRequires the Tinkers' Anvil to craft.
encyclopedia.tier1.body=Choose a material to learn more.
encyclopedia.tier1.title=Tier 1 Materials
encyclopedia.tier1_traits.body=Cultivation%1Increases the chance of obtaining more items from crops when harvesting.%1%1Summoner%1Stone and End Stone have a rare chance to spawn Silverfish and Endermites, respectively.%1%1Undead%1Striking undead mobs like zombies and husks transforms them into skeletons. Additionally, all defeated mobs now drop bones and bonemeal.
encyclopedia.tier2.body=Choose a material to learn more.
encyclopedia.tier2.title=Tier 2 Materials
encyclopedia.tier2_traits.body=Magnetic%1Creates a magnetic field that attracts materials.%1%1Speed%1Channels a rush of energy, granting heightened speed when wielded.%1%1Tasty%1When used, grants high saturation for an extended period, reducing hunger depletion.%1%1Experienced%1Increases the amount of experience you get from defeating mobs and mining ores.
encyclopedia.tier3.body=Choose a material to learn more.
encyclopedia.tier3.title=Tier 3 Materials
encyclopedia.tier3_traits.body=Killager%1Defeating Villagers/Pillagers can reward you with Emeralds. Whilst potentially granting you the "Hero of the Village"%1%1Smeltery%1Boosts efficiency by automatically smelting mined blocks. And provides a fiery defense, burning enemies on contact.%1%1Stuck%1A crippling strike slows your enemies, hindering their escape and attack speed.%1%1Soulbound%1Your most prized tools and weapons stay bound to your spirit, preventing loss on death.%1%1Diamond%1Infuses your tools and weapons with enhanced durability, making them resistant to wear and tear.
encyclopedia.tier4.body=Choose a material to learn more.
encyclopedia.tier4.title=Tier 4 Materials
encyclopedia.tier4_traits.body=Bounce%1Soar to new heights! Wielding this trait grants a powerful jump boost and a soft landing in most cases.%1%1Plunder%1Slain foes shower you with riches, with a chance for their loot to become more plentiful.%1%1Floaty%1Your attacks pack such a punch, they send foes on a one-way trip to the stratosphere.%1%1Guarding%1Stand your ground! This trait absorbs the force of blows, keeping you steady in combat.
encyclopedia.tools.body=Unleash your inner tinkerer and forge powerful tools in Tinkers' Construct!%1%1This Add-On allows you to craft and customize a wide variety of tools to fit your specific needs and playstyle.%1%1Here's a breakdown of the tools you can create:
encyclopedia.tools.title=Tools
